Hours will be reduced at a Lincolnshire swimming pool because of "essential" repairs during the summer holidays.The pool at Bourne Leisure Centre will undergo a series of temporary closures on weekdays between 12 August and 4 September.Early morning and evening sessions will be retained and the gym, studio and sports hall will operate as usual, South Kesteven District Council said.A spokesperson for LeisureSK, which operates the centre, said roof coverings would be repaired and new roof lights installed.
